I'm going to talk about my best friend's fitness habit, which is something I really want to develop myself.
Her name is An, and we've been close friends for over three years. She's a very cheerful and friendly person, with a lovely smile that makes people feel comfortable around her.
About a year ago, she decided to start going to the gym regularly. At that time, she felt quite insecure about her appearance and wanted to improve her body shape. So, she made a firm decision to adopt a healthier lifestyle.
At first, I didn't take it seriously because I thought it was just a temporary idea. However, it turned out that she was extremely committed. She goes to the gym almost everyday and usually spends at least an hour working out, no matter how busy she is. She even signed up for a training program with a personal trainer to achieve better results. On top of that, she follows a low-carb diet and carefully monitors what she eats.
As a result, she managed to lose around 15 kilograms in just three months, which I find truly impressive. Now, she looks much fitter and more confident than before.
There are several reasons why I would like to develop this habit. First, I've gained some weight recently, so I really need to get back in shape. Second, her transformation has inspired me a lot. Seeing her progress makes be believe that I can achieve similar results if I stay disciplined. Finally, regular exercise is beneficial not only for physical health but also for mental well-being, so I think it's a habit worth developing.
